Package: bsync
Type: Package
Title: Behavioral Synchrony Analyses
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Jeffrey", "Girard", email = "me@jmgirard.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for analyzing interpersonal and behavioral
    synchrony in continuous time series data. Provides highly efficient, C++ backed
    implementations of windowed cross-correlation (WCC) and peak-picking algorithms
    to quantify nonstationary lead-lag relationships. Includes a complete preprocessing
    pipeline for behavioral data featuring zero-phase smoothing, time-bin aggregation,
    and kinematic velocity and speed calculations. Additionally, the package supports
    rigorous null-hypothesis testing through circular-shift surrogate data generation
    (pseudo-synchrony analysis) to distinguish genuine interaction from spurious correlation.
